@startuml
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
skinparam maxMessageSize 160

title Chess Coach — P2P Multiplayer: Signaling + Move Exchange (proposed)

participant "Player A WebView\n(UI)" as UIA
participant "A Service\n(peer + signaling)" as SVCA
participant "Signaling\n(Cloudflare DO/WS)" as SIG
participant "STUN / TURN" as ICE
participant "B Service\n(peer + signaling)" as SVCB
participant "Player B WebView\n(UI)" as UIB

== Pairing / signaling ==

UIA -> SVCA : create game (room code / link)
SVCA -> SIG : open WSS, register room
UIB -> SVCB : join room <code>
SVCB -> SIG : open WSS, join room
SIG --> SVCA : peer joined

SVCA -> ICE : gather candidates (STUN; TURN if needed)
SVCA -> SIG : SDP offer + ICE candidates
SIG --> SVCB : relay offer + candidates
SVCB -> ICE : gather candidates
SVCB -> SIG : SDP answer + ICE candidates
SIG --> SVCA : relay answer + candidates

note over SVCA, SVCB
  Signaling only brokers SDP/ICE. Once the
  DataChannel opens, signaling is idle until
  reconnect. Direct P2P when NAT allows; TURN
  relays otherwise (common on cellular).
end note

SVCA <--> SVCB : **DataChannel OPEN** (P2P or TURN-relayed)

== In-game move exchange ==

UIA -> UIA : human plays move (validated locally, chess.js)
UIA -> SVCA : move {san, uci, fenAfter}
SVCA -> SVCB : DataChannel: move
SVCB -> UIB : apply opponent move to board
note over UIB
  Maia is NOT invoked — the opponent is human.
  B's local Stockfish/WebLLM may still run hints
  + coach commentary on the new position.
end note
UIB -> UIB : (optional) local eval + coach advice

UIB -> SVCB : human replies move
SVCB -> SVCA : DataChannel: move
SVCA -> UIA : apply opponent move

== Lifecycle / resume ==

note over SVCA
  Peer + signaling socket live in the foreground
  service, so WebView recreation (rotation,
  backgrounding) does not drop the connection.
  Service persists FEN/move history for resume.
end note

UIA -> SVCA : WebView recreated -> re-attach
SVCA --> UIA : replay current game state

@enduml
